BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Untitled-design-11.png
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260603T110322Z
DESCRIPTION:Horticultural Building\, Lal Bagh\, Wiele Studio\, Late 19th-Early 20th century\, Albumen print\, PHY.21244.8.1\nJoin us at the exhibition Paper Gardens: Art\, Botany and Empire\, and unravel the entangled histories of colonial-era classification of the natural world through botanical illustration. Drawing on select illustrations from the exhibition\, Abhishek Khan discusses the roles and aesthetics of gardens and garden-making\, and their colonial preference over native sacred groves.  He goes on to examine how these images emerged from masculine frameworks and compares them to native botanical art and contemporary works by women artists.
DTEND:20260614T120000Z
DTSTART:20260614T110000Z
SUMMARY:Aesthetics of Power
UID:1298@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/aesthetics-of-power/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Nocturnes-still-1-scaled.jpg
CATEGORIES:Film Screenings,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260604T072802Z
DESCRIPTION:Image credits: Metamorphosis Film Junction\nAn immersive viewing experience of sound and imagery\, the film weaves together an intricate and poetic tapestry of our world. In the dense forests of Arunachal Pradesh\, ecologist Mansi sets out on a quest to study moths in one of the most vibrant places on earth. She teams up with Bicki\, a young man from the indigenous Bugun community\, to seek clues about what the future holds for the moths as temperatures rise. \n\nBy focusing on a small\, ephemeral\, nocturnal creature like the moth\, Nocturnes seeks to question a human-centric view of the world. The lush forest\, throbbing with a vast diversity of life\, emerges as a breath-taking character as the film responds to the symphony of sounds and the inherent rhythms of the trees\, the wind and the rain. The result is a rare and transformative experience that invites us all to look with more attention and care at the hidden interconnections in nature. \n\nThis event is held in conjunction with our ongoing permanent exhibition Beneath the Turning Sky. 
DTEND:20260619T140000Z
DTSTART:20260619T123000Z
SUMMARY:Nocturnes
UID:1300@map-india.org
